<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4677081>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 31. Janthina globosa (Swainson), Pliocene (Piacenzian– Gelasian), Bowden, Jamaica (USNM135575), specimen recorded by Woodring (1928: 405); basal fragment of last whorl showing sinus in growth lines (camera lucida drawing); greatest diameter 4.2 mm. Scale bar 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4677081/files/figure.png" .

