<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4677079>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 30. Specimens of Janthina globosa (Swainson). (A–B) GNS RM5222, Waipu Cove, Northland, New Zealand, SEM; apical views of shell (A) and protoconch (B), showing smooth teleoconch surface, and protoconch inclined only weakly. (C–E) Monterosato’s type material, photos sent by M. Appolloni (MCZR) and M. Oliverio (University of Rome 1 “La Sapienza”); C, E, MCZR23423/1, lectotype designated here ofJanthina splendens Monterosato;Alexandria, Egypt; D, MCZR23414/1, lectotype designated here of Amethistina laeta Monterosato; Algeria. (F–G) ZMB41985a, lectotype designated here of Janthina patula Philippi, 1844, from Naples, Italy; photos sent by C. Zorn (ZMB). Scale bars:A, 3 mm; B, 200 µm; C–G, 10 mm (longer bar applies to C–E, shorter bar to F–G)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4677079/files/figure.png" .

